cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper proposes a novel model for recommender systems that focuses on learning feature interactions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also specifically mentions the application of the model to recommender systems, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper introduces an attention network and deep learning variants, which are common in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a sampling scheme, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed model on two well-known datasets, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
